          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "MakeLinkServerDirectoryAndFile",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are used to encapsulate logic that can be reused across queries. This function is designed to construct a directory and file path for a linked server, which is a server-to-server connection in SQL Server that allows for querying and managing data across different servers."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
